    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="323"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d323">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5914/46½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                        Acting Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Polk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">30 September, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Polk</hi>: Thank you for sending me the
                        enclosed.<note n="2" xml:id="d323fn1">Telegram No. 173, Sept. 16, 1915, from
                        the minister in Denmark, <ref target="frus1917#pg_595">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 595</ref>.</note> This is a matter I am
                    keenly interested in and hope we can follow up in the right way and at the right
                    moment to a consummation. Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
